    "125859128": {
      "title": "Approximate Dynamic Programming",
      "abstract": "This chapter contains a brief review of dynamic programming in continuous time and space. In particular, traditional dynamic programming algorithms such as policy iteration, value iteration, and actor-critic methods are presented in the context of continuous-time optimal control. The role of the optimal value function as a Lyapunov function is explained to facilitate online closed-loop optimal control. This chapter also highlights the problems and the limitations of existing techniques, thereby motivating the development in this book. The chapter concludes with some historic remarks and a brief classification of the available dynamic programming techniques."
